---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Viking Pest Control Alternative NJ | Cloakd"
  description="Viking Pest Control covers NJ with SMART digital monitoring. Tracking activity is one layer. Here's the layer that reduces how fast rodents come back between treatment visits."
  path="/vs/viking-pest-control"
>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── HERO ── -->
  <section class="pt-20 pb-24 px-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">
        Viking Pest Control vs. Cloakd
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-8">
        Viking Pest Control monitors NJ rodent activity digitally around the clock.<br />
        Monitoring what's there is one layer. Here's the layer that reduces how fast it comes back.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Viking Pest Control is one of the dominant commercial pest operators
        in New Jersey — 45 years in the market, state-certified licensed pest
        management professionals, and SMART digital monitoring technology
        that tracks rodent activity year-round. Their program is well-executed.
        It doesn't reduce the fertility of the replacement colony that
        forms after each treatment cycle. That's what the fertility
        management layer addresses.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── WHAT VIKING COVERS ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        What Viking's program covers
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        SMART monitoring tracks the population. It doesn't change how fast it rebuilds.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            Viking's SMART Rodent Control uses digital sensors that monitor
            rodent activity 525,600 minutes per year — transmitting data
            continuously to track population presence and density. Combined
            with state-certified licensed pest management professionals and
            flexible scheduling, it's the most technologically advanced
            standard rodent control program operating in NJ.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            Digital monitoring tracks what's there. Treatment removes it.
            Neither changes the underlying biology: Norway rats in NJ
            commercial and residential areas detect empty territory within
            days of a colony being cleared. The food source remains,
            the harborage points remain, and the replacement population
            moves in on the same timeline regardless of how accurately
            the previous population was monitored.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            For NJ restaurant operators under the NJ Food Code (NJ
            Administrative Code 8:24), the compliance risk is the same:
            a municipal health department inspector who arrives during
            week six after a treatment cycle will find active signs.
            Reducing how fast the replacement colony reaches detectable
            density is what changes that outcome.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            {
              label: 'What Viking covers',
              items: [
                'SMART digital rodent monitoring — year-round activity tracking',
                'State-certified licensed pest management professionals',
                'Commercial and residential programs across NJ, PA, DE, MD',
                'Flexible scheduling including after-hours and weekend visits',
                'Licensed treatment and compliance documentation',
              ],
              positive: true,
            },
            {
              label: 'What standard treatment leaves open',
              items: [
                'Replacement colony forming 4–8 weeks after treatment',
                'Population fertility between scheduled visits',
                'Documented declining trend for NJ health department re-inspection',
                'Fertility management to reduce replacement rate',
              ],
              positive: false,
            },
          ].map(({ label, items, positive }) => (
            <div class={`rounded-xl p-6 ${positive ? 'bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8' : 'bg-white border border-[#c96a3a]/15'}`}>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#1c1814]/45 mb-4">{label}</p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                {items.map((item) => (
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <div class={`w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5 ${positive ? 'bg-[#7aab7e]/15' : 'bg-[#1c1814]/8'}`}>
                      {positive
                        ? <svg width="10" height="8" viewBox="0 0 10 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 4L3.5 6.5L9 1" stroke="#5e9263" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
                        : <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 8 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L7 7M7 1L1 7" stroke="#1c1814" stroke-opacity="0.3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                      }
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">{item}</p>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── COMPARISON TABLE ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        Side-by-side comparison
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Viking Pest Control vs. Cloakd 90-day program
      </h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[#1c1814]/10">
              <th class="py-4 pr-6 text-sm font-semibold text-[#1c1814]/45 uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Feature</th>
              <th class="py-4 pr-6 text-sm font-semibold text-[#1c1814]/45 uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Viking Pest Control</th>
              <th class="py-4 text-sm font-semibold text-[#c96a3a] uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Cloakd (added layer)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ['Treatment method', 'Licensed treatment + SMART digital monitoring technology', 'Evolve fertility management — gossypol-based soft bait that reduces reproductive output'],
              ['Monitoring', 'SMART sensors — digital data transmitted continuously', 'Monthly track count plates — documented declining trend specific to 90-day compliance record'],
              ['Replacement cycle', 'Cleared at treatment, rebuilds 4–8 weeks later', 'Replacement population forms at reduced rate — density declines between visits'],
              ['NJ compliance record', 'Licensed PMP documentation for NJ health department inspections', 'Written monthly monitoring reports — 90-day trend line for municipal health officer'],
              ['Re-inspection risk', 'Dependent on timing of next NJ health inspection vs. last treatment', 'Reduced — documented declining population, not cycling'],
              ['Works with existing vendor', 'Is your existing NJ vendor', 'Yes — Viking handles Phase 1, Cloakd adds the fertility layer'],
            ].map(([feature, viking, cloakd]) => (
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1c1814]/8">
                <td class="py-4 pr-6 text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814]">{feature}</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-6 text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{viking}</td>
                <td class="py-4 text-base text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">{cloakd}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── FIELD DATA ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        What the fertility layer produces
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Monitoring shows what's there. Fertility management reduces how much comes back.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
        {[
          { value: '79%', label: 'reduction in rodent track presence', sub: 'Location A — 5-month urban building deployment, Aug 2025 to Jan 2026', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '88%', label: 'drop in track density at the same site', sub: 'Tracks per monitoring plate declined even at stations with residual activity', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '50%+', label: 'reduction at a second independent site', sub: 'Same 5-month period, different urban building profile', color: '#7aab7e' },
        ].map(({ value, label, sub, color }) => (
          <div class="bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8 rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-5xl font-bold mb-3" style={`color:${color}`}>{value}</p>
            <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] leading-snug mb-2">{label}</p>
            <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-[#1c1814]/40 max-w-2xl">
        Source: <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/senestech-reports-significant-reductions-in-rodent-activity-following-evolve-deployments-in-urban-field-studies-302691116.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-[#1c1814]/65 transition-colors">SenesTech, Inc. — February 18, 2026</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── WHO SHOULD USE EACH ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        How to think about it
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Viking tracks and treats. Cloakd reduces what keeps rebuilding.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-8">
          <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] mb-4">Viking alone is sufficient if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              'You have a single active infestation with no recurring NJ violation history',
              'Your NJ municipal health inspection timing has been consistently favorable',
              'You need licensed treatment and digital monitoring documentation',
              'Your property doesn\'t have the surrounding density pressure driving fast replacement',
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#7aab7e] flex-shrink-0 mt-2"></div>
                <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65">{item}</p>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-8">
          <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] mb-4">Add Cloakd if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              'You\'ve had recurring NJ rodent violations despite consistent Viking service',
              'You need a documented 90-day trend line for a NJ municipal health re-inspection',
              'The replacement cycle keeps resetting between treatment visits',
              'Your NJ health officer wants evidence of population decline, not just treatment records',
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#c96a3a]/50 flex-shrink-0 mt-2"></div>
                <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65">{item}</p>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── CTA ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6">
          Viking stays. The fertility layer goes on top.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Tell us about your NJ property and what the recurring problem
          looks like. We'll outline what the 90-day program adds on top
          of your current service.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a
            href="/get-started"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold rounded bg-[#b85530] text-[#faf8f4] hover:bg-[#c96a3a] transition-colors"
          >
            Start the 90-day program
          </a>
          <a
            href="/nj-rodent-violation"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-medium rounded border border-[#1c1814]/15 text-[#1c1814]/70 hover:text-[#1c1814] hover:border-[#1c1814]/25 transition-colors"
          >
            NJ rodent violations
          </a>
          <a
            href="/how-it-works"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-medium rounded border border-[#1c1814]/15 text-[#1c1814]/70 hover:text-[#1c1814] hover:border-[#1c1814]/25 transition-colors"
          >
            How it works
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
